Class Summary
FNPTask class implements the CKK algorithm (Complete Karmarkar-Karp Algorithm) for 2-way Number Partitioning, due to Richard Korf (1997).
FNPTask2 class implements the CKK algorithm (Complete Karmarkar-Karp Algorithm) for 2-way Number Partitioning, due to Richard Korf (1997).
FNPTask3 class implements the CKK algorithm (Complete Karmarkar-Karp Algorithm) for 2-way Number Partitioning, due to Richard Korf (1997).
NPTask class implements the CKK algorithm (Complete Karmarkar-Karp Algorithm) for 2-way Number Partitioning, due to Richard Korf (1997).
 

Package popt4jlib.NumberPartitioning Description

Package defines parallel/distributed versions of well-known Number Partitioning algorithms. Number Partitioning is NP-complete and is known to exhibit a phase-transition when m (the number of bits of each number in the list) approximately equals n (the number of numbers in the list to be partitioned).

Package Specification

A multi-threaded and a distributed version of the Complete Karmarkar-Karp (CKK) algorithm is implemented as specified by Korf (1997).
